onary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Christina .  It was popular in the medieval period, when it appears to have been used interchangeably with   Christian  , and again in Britain at the end of the 19th century. In the United States it was particularly popular from the 1950s to the 1970s."],"variants":[{"name":"Christeen","meanings":["form of   Christina .  It was popular in the medieval period, when it appears to have been used interchangeably with   Christian  , and again in Britain at the end of the 19th century. In the United States it was particularly popular from the 1950s to the 1970s."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Christine Kilbane was born in 1225, in Ayrshire, Scotland. She married Adam Wallace - Laird of Riccarton and Kyle in 1245, in Ayrshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1250, in South Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 25, and was buried in Ayrshire, Scotland."},"et":{"1225–1250":"1225–1250","1197–1250":"1197–1250","1249–1307":"1249–1307","1249":"1249","1225":"1225","9 April 1249":"9. aprill 1249","1245":"1245","1197":"1197","1250":"1250","1307":"1307","Riccarton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Riccarton, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","South Ayrshire, Scotland":"South Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1225–1250":"1225–1250","1197–1250":"1197–1250","1249–1307":"1249–1307","1249":"1249","1225":"1225","9 April 1249":"9. huhtikuuta 1249","1245":"1245","1197":"1197","1250":"1250","1307":"1307","Riccarton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Riccarton, Ayrshire, Scotland","Ayr, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayr, Ayrshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","South Ayrshire, Scotland":"South Ayrshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1225–1250":"1225–1250","1197–1250":"1197–1250","1249–1307":"1249–1307","1249":"1249","1225":"1225","9 